@andrenatal I've made a WIP commit f1d697a addressing this issue. It's not finished but the majority of the code is there. The largest pain was having to write the queue and threading code by hand.

As a warning, do no try to use the standard TensorFlow Queues and Readers[[1]](https://www.tensorflow.org/versions/r0.11/how_tos/reading_data/index.html#reading-from-files). They will not work. 

As we require paddings, we would have to use a [PaddingFIFOQueue](https://www.tensorflow.org/versions/r0.11/api_docs/python/io_ops.html#PaddingFIFOQueue). However, a [PaddingFIFOQueue](https://www.tensorflow.org/versions/r0.11/api_docs/python/io_ops.html#PaddingFIFOQueue) doesn't allow the other thing we require SparseTensors, as TensorFlow's Queues do not work with SparseTensors[[2]](https://www.tensorflow.org/versions/r0.11/how_tos/reading_data/index.html#sparse-input-data). So this basically means we have to write the code by hand as I did.

