Dear paddywwoof, I am not sure if you already made the steps from the bitbucket project (https://bitbucket.org/Nodrev/kivy-python-for-android-with-ctypes/commits/30948f20cef489dba165b3b33aefccbb5f400b84#chg-recipes/python/recipe.sh). Then you can take a look at the cross compiling log and check what is the error. if you put only  python in the distribute line you will get less logs than usual. If there is any error during cross compiling then the ctypes.so will not be created. Unfortunately the process does not stop if a subcomponent is not compiling, the developer has to dig into the log.
In the end you should see the _ctypes.so in $BUID_python/build/lib.linux-x86_64-2.7, then you can try to add the lines:  
cd $BUILD_python
try cp -a build/lib.linux-x86_64-2.7/_ctypes*.so $LIBS_PATH

in the python recipe to copy the library to dist/default/private/lib/python2.7/lib-dynload.

Then you can add in PythonService.java the line referring to ctypes:
try {
                 System.load(getFilesDir() + "/lib/python2.7/lib-dynload/libcrypto.so.1.0.0");
                 System.load(getFilesDir() + "/lib/python2.7/lib-dynload/libssl.so.1.0.0");
                 System.load(getFilesDir() + "/lib/python2.7/lib-dynload/_ctypes.so");
} catch(UnsatisfiedLinkError e) {
}

