@ttim pointed out that for many mid-graph Subject values, the Scheduler should not actually have the outputs... instead, they should go straight into storage so that the next worker can pick them up and begin execution.

As of 87354a5b766032227e7b25ba93deaa8fd8e3e57f, the Scheduler is passing in a deserialized Subject via the StepRequest object, and then receives newly created Subjects via StepResult. Instead, the Scheduler doesn't actually need a reference to the Subject at all: only its key. In order to make that work without bouncing the content through the scheduler, we need shared storage for all workers.

So I think that this ticket might be invalid. If anything, having support for passing the subject from a caller to a recipient would only be an optimization... because it's unlikely that the caller has the content. I think focusing on #2968 instead would make the most sense.

